{"id": 232037322, "title": "FCT Board Prioritizes Pilgrims' Welfare, Wellbeing in Hajj 2024", "text": "ABUJA \u2013 The Nigerian Federal Capital Territory Muslims Pilgrims Welfare Board (MPWB) has reaffirmed its commitment to the welfare and wellbeing of its pilgrims in Saudi Arabia for Hajj 2024. Director Malam Abubakar Adamu Evuti assured that the Board will prioritize accommodations, food, and healthcare for the pilgrims throughout their stay in the Holy Land. Evuti emphasized that the Board will not compromise on the pilgrims\u2019 wellbeing, ensuring they receive the best provisions. In case of any health challenges beyond the Board\u2019s capacity, they will be referred to the National Hajj Commission of Nigeria (NAHCON) for immediate attention. The FCT pilgrims arrived in the holy land on May 15, 2024, and the Board has been providing for their needs since then. Evuti urged pilgrims to be ambassadors of Nigeria and refrain from spreading propaganda or misinformation on social media.", "summary": "<div style=\"margin-bottom:20px;\"><img width=\"474\" height=\"500\" src=\"https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240609-WA0044.jpg\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" alt=\"\" decoding=\"async\" fetchpriority=\"high\" srcset=\"https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240609-WA0044.jpg 474w, https://independent.ng/wp-content/uploads/IMG-20240609-WA0044-284x300.jpg 284w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 474px) 100vw, 474px\" /></div>ABUJA &#8211; The Nigerian Federal Capital Territory Muslims Pilgrims Welfare Board (MPWB) has reaffirmed its commitment to the welfare and wellbeing of its pilgrims in Saudi Arabia for Hajj 2024. Director Malam Abubakar Adamu Evuti assured that the Board will prioritize accommodations, food, and healthcare for the pilgrims throughout their stay in the Holy Land. [&#8230;]", "url": "https://independent.ng/fct-board-prioritizes-pilgrims-welfare-wellbeing-in-hajj-2024/", "image": "https://independent.n